@node "HISTORY" "History"
 
    
    @{b}@{u}HISTORY:@{uu}@{ub}

    
    · 1.0 - Internal:
      > only buttons for playing single tracks, max 40 tracks
    · 1.1 - Internal:
      > added "Play" which allows to play all tracks
      > added "Stop" which allows to stop playing tracks
      > added "Vol -|+" which allows to set the volume
    · 1.2 - Internal:
      > added "Track" which allows to set the track number
      > added "-|+" for tracks which allow to increase/decrease the track number
      > added "Format" - 8SVX, WAV and MAUD are supported
      > added "Mode" - 16BIT, MONO and MUTE are supported
    · 1.3 - Internal:
      > added "File" which allows to set the output file for the track
      > added "Save track" which allows to save the track
    · 1.4 - Public: (FreeWare)
      > reworked the code, now EasyACDDA is much better
      > added the AIFF file format
      > added a background image into the window (400x200 pixels)
      > added the tooltype "IMAGE" which allows to change the background image
      > added the menu item "About" which gives you some infos about EasyACDDA
      > supplied a install-script that makes your life easy
    · 1.5ß (Rev. 1,2 and 3) - Internal:
      > reworked the code in order to make EasyACDDA more flexible
      > added the configuration panel for CDRom
      > added the test panel for CDRom
      > added the menu item "Config." for the configuration panel
      > added the menu item "Test" for the test panel
      > added the menu item "Quit" which allows to quit EasyACCDA
      > added the tooltype "PLAN" (default "e")
      > added the tooltype "VOL" (default "100[%]")
      > added the tooltype "FORMAT" (default "8SVX")
      > added the tooltype "MODE" (default "16BIT")
      > added the tooltype "FILE" (default "DH1:Example.wav")
      > added the tooltype "DEVICE" (default "atapi.device")
      > added the tooltype "UNIT" (default "1")
      > added the tooltype "MEMTYPE" (default "512")
      > added some routines which make EasyACDDA more interactive
      > now when you are saving a track the other functions appear disabled
    · 1.6 - Public: (GiftWare)
      > added the tooltype "NOMEMTYPE" (default "FALSE")
      > found another way to address commands (more safe)
      > reworked the menu item "About". There are two gads ("Okay|SendEmail")
      > the gad "SendEMail" calls  your favorite emailer in order to  contact me
        but for this feature you need the latest OpenURL installed/configured
      > added some internal help messages for panels
      > supplied an alternative background image for AGA sistems (5bit)
      > supplied a standard  installer-script which  allows to install EasyACDDA
        without problems (instead of the install-script)
      > no debug output
      > small internal changes
      > added a sort of manual to the readme
    · 1.7 - Public: (EuroWare)
      > previous versions crashed when another task was going to run. Fixed
      > optimized the code using some efficient routines
      > small minor changes
    · 1.8 - Public: (GiftWare)
      > added the menu item "Infos" which allows to access to the CD contents
      > the "Table of Contents" is  interactive, by clicking on one of the lines
        which compose the list a track will be played.
      > added an appicon so EasyACDDA is able to work while iconified, too !
      > small minor changes
    · 1.8.1 - Public:
      > each window is able to access to the main menu
      > there is a simple clock without the date
      > improved the gui (small small changes) regarding the buttons for tracks
      > changed the email address for OpenURL and "About" window
      > improved the installer-script
      > updated the readme
    · 1.8.2 - Public:
      > some small optimizations
      > changed the the default value in the track box (1 instead of 0)
      > added my URL in the program and readme
      > updated the readme especially the section "LEGAL"
    · 1.8.3 - Public:
      > added a guide for a easy use of EasyACDDA
    · 1.9 - Public:
      > reworked the installer in order to install PNG icons too!


@endnode
@node "PROBLEMS" "Problems"
 
 
    @{b}@{u}KNOWN PROBLEMS:@{uu}@{ub}

    
    When you are saving a track do not open the  window "Table of Contents" (See
    "Infos") otherwise your  system will  crash. This  problem affects my system
    and I don't know if this problem may affect your system (I hope no !).
    This problem may be due to the fact that when you are saving a track the CPU
    is quite busy.
 

@endnode
